Rating: 4
I made this without mint (I thought I bought it but can't find it). I used a mandoline to slice the fennel and onion thinly. I was afraid the onions were still too sharp even after the ice bath, but the dressing made them more mellow. This would be a nice winter time first course and a nice change of pace from lettuce-based salad. Not many people have had raw fennel so it's also nice that has something unique in it.

Rating: 4
This is a favorite in our house -- very refreshing and great with paella. I do toast the coriander seeds per the recipe and think it's worthwhile. I quarter the sliced oranges, onion, and fennel and toss them together with the dressing in a big bowl, which makes the dish easier to eat IMO. It's OK to make this a little in advance but add the mint at the last minute.

Rating: 4
I have made this salad a few times and it always gets great reviews. I leave out the mint as I usually serve it as a condiment for fish tacos.

